Configure the SSH Hostname

. Add a Public Hostname: On the "Configure" screen, click Add a public hostname.
2. Fill in the fields for Domain SSH:
• Subdomain: Choose a subdomain for SSH access (e.g., ssh).
• Domain: Select the domain name you are using with Cloudflare.
• Type: Select SSH.
• URL: Enter the local destination for your SSH server, which is localhost:22.

Set Up Zero Trust Access (Security)
This is the most critical security step. It ensures only you can connect.
1. Go to Access: From the left-hand menu, click Access -> Applications.

Create a Policy (The Rule):
• Policy Name: Allow Only Me
• Action: Allow
• Rule (Include): Set the selector to Emails and enter your specific email address (freedomcode@icloud.com).
• Click Next.
5. Enable Browser-Rendered Terminal (Web SSH):

uname -m


